WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.053 --> 00:00:09.102
- Oh. wait. wait. Zoe.
- What happened?

2
00:00:09.126 --> 00:00:10.836
- She's been poisoned.
- What?

3
00:00:10.860 --> 00:00:12.672
I have to assume I'm hot.

4
00:00:12.696 --> 00:00:15.479
There's an antidote. but they've got it.

5
00:00:15.503 --> 00:00:16.614
My only chance

6
00:00:16.638 --> 00:00:18.485
<i>is to let 'em take me.</i>

7
00:00:18.509 --> 00:00:20.656
<i>The deal is off.
Someone has moved against me.</i>

8
00:00:20.680 --> 00:00:22.893
<i>I have not the time to determine</i>

9
00:00:22.917 --> 00:00:25.465
<i>whether you are part of it.</i>

10
00:00:25.489 --> 00:00:27.503
<i>so I will assume it</i>

11
00:00:27.527 --> 00:00:29.393
<i>and proceed accordingly.</i>

12
00:00:29.418 --> 00:00:30.699
Zoe.

13
00:00:30.724 --> 00:00:32.941
Harold Harper sent me.
Make sure you were okay.

14
00:00:32.966 --> 00:00:34.130
Are you coming?

15
00:00:34.154 --> 00:00:35.419
Hello. Marion.

16
00:00:35.443 --> 00:00:36.754
<i>I know about the cartel.</i>

17
00:00:36.778 --> 00:00:38.925
I know about the Meshbahar deposit.

18
00:00:38.949 --> 00:00:41.798
Faraz Hamzad would
not entertain any of our offers.

19
00:00:41.822 --> 00:00:44.036
To exploit the Meshbahar deposits

20
00:00:44.060 --> 00:00:47.443
for years. decades.
and to keep it stable.

21
00:00:47.467 --> 00:00:49.580
<i>you need another kind of partner.</i>

22
00:00:49.604 --> 00:00:51.951
I was helping you rescue Parwana Hamzad

23
00:00:51.975 --> 00:00:54.190
because I wanted you to introduce me

24
00:00:54.214 --> 00:00:56.651
<i>to Parwana Hamzad.</i>

25
00:01:04.234 --> 00:01:09.552
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

26
00:01:09.577 --> 00:01:11.123
<i>Dad?</i>

27
00:01:12.016 --> 00:01:13.996
<i>Yeah?</i>

28
00:01:14.020 --> 00:01:16.501
<i>Can you take me off speaker?</i>

29
00:01:16.525 --> 00:01:18.995
<i>Yeah. I'm-I'm here.</i>

30
00:01:21.468 --> 00:01:23.577
I need you to do something for me.

31
00:01:24.911 --> 00:01:26.454
<i>What is it?</i>

32
00:01:28.482 --> 00:01:30.667
I need you to accept this.

33
00:01:34.026 --> 00:01:36.048
Why this is happening.

34
00:01:37.273 --> 00:01:38.967
Why it happened.

35
00:01:42.596 --> 00:01:44.473
I found something here.

36
00:01:46.851 --> 00:01:48.932
This family is important to me.

37
00:01:50.660 --> 00:01:52.696
That much is true.

38
00:01:59.744 --> 00:02:03.171
And this is not a rejection
of you or of Mom.

39
00:02:03.195 --> 00:02:04.878
That much is also true.

40
00:02:04.902 --> 00:02:07.125
Promise me that you're gonna
find a way to accept this.

41
00:02:07.149 --> 00:02:08.905
I need to know
that you're not gonna spend

42
00:02:08.929 --> 00:02:11.244
the rest of your life resenting this.

43
00:02:11.268 --> 00:02:13.114
Resenting me for this

44
00:02:13.138 --> 00:02:14.877
or resenting this family for this.

45
00:02:17.146 --> 00:02:19.227
I am asking you to accept...

46
00:02:19.251 --> 00:02:22.022
...that this is something that I wanted.

47
00:02:22.046 --> 00:02:23.158
Can you do that for me?

48
00:02:23.825 --> 00:02:25.372
Can you do that for me. please?

49
00:02:25.396 --> 00:02:28.168
Shit. Shit. No. wait!

50
00:02:51.581 --> 00:02:53.061
...Hamzad.

51
00:02:53.085 --> 00:02:55.365
...Hamzad... Hamzad.

52
00:02:57.760 --> 00:02:59.540
I'm the only Hamzad.

53
00:02:59.564 --> 00:03:00.975
Hamzad.

54
00:03:00.999 --> 00:03:02.546
Hamzad.

55
00:03:02.570 --> 00:03:04.450
I'm the only Hamzad.

56
00:03:04.474 --> 00:03:05.518
I'm the only Hamzad!

57
00:03:05.542 --> 00:03:06.955
Hamzad?

58
00:03:06.979 --> 00:03:08.524
I'm the only Hamzad.

59
00:03:08.548 --> 00:03:09.927
I'm the only Hamzad.

60
00:03:09.951 --> 00:03:11.931
I'm the only Hamzad.

61
00:03:13.792 --> 00:03:16.864
...Hamzad...

62
00:03:21.714 --> 00:03:23.613
Faraz Hamzad is dead.

63
00:03:25.175 --> 00:03:27.010
I am his daughter.

64
00:03:29.758 --> 00:03:31.036
Who are they?

65
00:03:31.060 --> 00:03:32.956
No one who matters to you.

66
00:03:34.534 --> 00:03:36.209
He had a sister.

67
00:03:37.332 --> 00:03:39.205
But you just killed her.

68
00:03:40.806 --> 00:03:44.346
So I am the only one left
who knew his business.

69
00:03:45.489 --> 00:03:49.222
Leave them alone. and I will help you.

70
00:03:50.390 --> 00:03:53.314
Help me? How?

71
00:03:53.338 --> 00:03:56.354
I will tell you everything you
want to know about this place.

72
00:03:56.378 --> 00:03:57.856
How it works.

73
00:03:57.880 --> 00:03:59.775
Where things are hidden.

74
00:04:00.586 --> 00:04:02.266
The things you will need to know

75
00:04:02.290 --> 00:04:05.495
that will take you forever to find out.

76
00:04:07.354 --> 00:04:08.742
I will tell you.

77
00:05:03.545 --> 00:05:06.424
I have orders to separate the family.

78
00:05:07.626 --> 00:05:09.344
To eliminate them.

79
00:05:11.455 --> 00:05:13.642
No one will know you're here.

80
00:05:14.300 --> 00:05:19.310
If you lie. no one will see you again.

81
00:05:27.126 --> 00:05:28.947
Write what you know.

82
00:05:33.003 --> 00:05:35.453
How can I be sure the others are safe?

83
00:07:23.025 --> 00:07:24.560
<i>Da.</i>

84
00:07:27.466 --> 00:07:28.942
<i>Da.</i>

85
00:07:38.055 --> 00:07:39.452
<i>Da.</i>

86
00:13:27.307 --> 00:13:29.143
The Russians.

87
00:13:29.733 --> 00:13:31.290
They lost the mine.

88
00:13:31.314 --> 00:13:32.694
Yes.

89
00:13:32.718 --> 00:13:34.586
- To who?
- It's unclear.

90
00:13:35.354 --> 00:13:38.438
Well. maybe. but that's not
what they just said to you.

91
00:13:38.462 --> 00:13:40.075
Not all of it.

92
00:13:40.099 --> 00:13:41.544
Who took the mine?

93
00:13:41.568 --> 00:13:44.350
A particularly determined group
of local fighters

94
00:13:44.374 --> 00:13:47.599
seems to have eliminated
the Russians at the site.

95
00:13:50.821 --> 00:13:52.423
Yeah. and?

96
00:13:52.813 --> 00:13:57.033
There are rumors
that they were led by a woman.

97
00:13:58.269 --> 00:14:00.279
An American woman.

98
00:14:03.479 --> 00:14:05.082
Angela.

99
00:14:05.451 --> 00:14:07.161
Angela's alive.

100
00:14:08.022 --> 00:14:09.935
Yes. but maybe not for long.

101
00:14:09.959 --> 00:14:13.241
Pavlovich is summoning reserves
from as far as Central Africa.

102
00:14:13.265 --> 00:14:15.379
Every man in his army
is to take the area back.

103
00:14:15.403 --> 00:14:17.339
Well. y-you can stop that happening.

104
00:14:17.880 --> 00:14:19.320
And why would I want to do that?

105
00:14:19.344 --> 00:14:20.656
Because you know it was a mistake

106
00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:22.784
to involve him in the first place.

107
00:14:23.218 --> 00:14:24.932
You know that Angela would be

108
00:14:24.956 --> 00:14:27.136
a better partner for you
in the long run.

109
00:14:27.160 --> 00:14:28.873
You told me that she would never
side with me.

110
00:14:28.897 --> 00:14:31.315
You told me that you would
never even permit me to try.

111
00:14:31.339 --> 00:14:33.314
Her life is at stake.

112
00:14:33.338 --> 00:14:35.743
I think Johnny's life might be at stake.

113
00:14:36.318 --> 00:14:39.276
There might not be any limit
to what I would do now.

114
00:14:50.205 --> 00:14:53.889
You know. you really have
got sharper. Harold.

115
00:14:53.913 --> 00:14:57.229
I'm sure that isn't true.
but just for a moment.

116
00:14:57.253 --> 00:15:00.125
I actually found myself believing you.

117
00:15:00.753 --> 00:15:02.723
Help me end this.

118
00:15:02.865 --> 00:15:07.640
We can fight about what happens
after that... after that.

119
00:15:10.714 --> 00:15:12.351
End it how?

120
00:15:29.392 --> 00:15:31.672
Do you think he's dead?

121
00:15:31.696 --> 00:15:34.244
- It's impossible to know.
- I know.

122
00:15:34.288 --> 00:15:36.860
I'm asking if you <i>think</i> he's dead.

123
00:15:37.853 --> 00:15:40.501
What difference does it make
what I think if I don't know?

124
00:15:40.526 --> 00:15:42.008
Because...

125
00:15:42.359 --> 00:15:45.881
one way. you might help me
find him and save him.

126
00:15:45.906 --> 00:15:48.220
and the other way.
you just pretend to help me

127
00:15:48.244 --> 00:15:51.617
for as long as you need me
to help you kill Pavlovich.

128
00:15:52.519 --> 00:15:54.121
I gave you my word.

129
00:15:54.556 --> 00:15:56.035
I may be new at this.

130
00:15:56.059 --> 00:15:58.631
but I know enough to know
what that's worth.

131
00:15:59.733 --> 00:16:02.064
The old man did that thing
with you. didn't he?

132
00:16:02.773 --> 00:16:04.452
What thing?

133
00:16:04.476 --> 00:16:07.257
His bullshit about
"the knife in one hand

134
00:16:07.281 --> 00:16:10.263
is like your empathy. and in the other."

135
00:16:10.287 --> 00:16:12.067
eh. s-something or the other.

136
00:16:12.091 --> 00:16:15.635
- Ruthlessness.
- Yes. that.

137
00:16:15.966 --> 00:16:18.648
- You're saying it isn't true?
- For him?

138
00:16:18.672 --> 00:16:20.518
Too true.

139
00:16:20.542 --> 00:16:23.891
I knew I couldn't trust a word
that came out of his mouth.

140
00:16:23.915 --> 00:16:26.763
or maybe it took a lot of practice

141
00:16:26.787 --> 00:16:28.824
to know which words to trust.

142
00:16:29.758 --> 00:16:33.109
Either way. that's the role
the game asked him to play.

143
00:16:33.133 --> 00:16:35.013
Fucking serpent.

144
00:16:36.205 --> 00:16:38.141
And there was no one better.

145
00:16:40.348 --> 00:16:42.027
But the old man knew any word

146
00:16:42.051 --> 00:16:45.107
that came out of my mouth
was written in stone.

147
00:16:46.159 --> 00:16:48.129
That's my role in the game.

148
00:16:52.322 --> 00:16:54.676
Help me get to Pavlovich.

149
00:16:55.512 --> 00:16:58.161
I'll help you find Dan Chase.

150
00:17:08.036 --> 00:17:09.473
Yeah.

151
00:17:10.508 --> 00:17:12.088
Copy that.

152
00:17:12.112 --> 00:17:14.015
We're ten minutes out.

153
00:17:15.317 --> 00:17:18.991
Whatever you're gonna do. do it quickly.

154
00:17:20.529 --> 00:17:22.575
He's closing in on the target.

155
00:17:22.599 --> 00:17:24.435
What do you want to do?

156
00:17:25.437 --> 00:17:27.284
I'm not asking you to do anything

157
00:17:27.308 --> 00:17:29.943
you don't want done already.

158
00:17:30.314 --> 00:17:33.196
Even if Pavlovich can
get himself out of this mess.

159
00:17:33.220 --> 00:17:35.501
how long before the next mess ends up

160
00:17:35.525 --> 00:17:38.798
being something impossible
for you to clean up?

161
00:17:39.244 --> 00:17:41.613
Impossible to unwind?

162
00:17:41.637 --> 00:17:43.340
"Impossible."

163
00:17:45.042 --> 00:17:48.493
For a man like you. that word
should be so hard to find.

164
00:17:48.517 --> 00:17:51.690
And yet it's always been
so available to you.

165
00:17:52.007 --> 00:17:55.742
To cultivate Angela Adams is impossible.

166
00:17:55.766 --> 00:17:59.281
To do clandestine work and raise
a family is impossible.

167
00:17:59.305 --> 00:18:04.058
I'm impossible to understand.
to please. to trust.

168
00:18:04.082 --> 00:18:06.062
But what an ambitious
young thing she is.

169
00:18:06.086 --> 00:18:07.814
How could I ever?

170
00:18:12.778 --> 00:18:15.146
Your default to absolutes
was always the part of you

171
00:18:15.170 --> 00:18:17.317
I found hardest to understand.

172
00:18:17.341 --> 00:18:20.189
Your aversion to them was mine.

173
00:18:20.213 --> 00:18:22.696
Some things should be absolute.

174
00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:24.456
What things?

175
00:18:24.748 --> 00:18:27.159
The things we owe people we love.

176
00:18:27.183 --> 00:18:30.568
they should be constant.
they should be inviolable.

177
00:18:31.004 --> 00:18:33.584
And the sacrifices that you
would make for Angela's sake.

178
00:18:33.608 --> 00:18:35.576
those are inviolable to you. too?

179
00:18:35.600 --> 00:18:36.757
Yes.

180
00:18:36.781 --> 00:18:39.486
No matter what it's about to cost you?

181
00:18:47.882 --> 00:18:50.857
You could've been a great man. Harold...

182
00:18:53.213 --> 00:18:56.988
...were you not so frightened
of disappointing anyone.

183
00:19:01.146 --> 00:19:02.744
Fuck you.

184
00:19:20.167 --> 00:19:21.503
We're moving.

185
00:19:22.113 --> 00:19:23.984
<i>I'll have instructions for you shortly</i>

186
00:19:24.008 --> 00:19:25.988
<i>how to approach the target.</i>

187
00:19:26.012 --> 00:19:27.390
Conference guest.

188
00:19:27.414 --> 00:19:30.420
_

189
00:19:49.726 --> 00:19:51.563
<i>Are you on-site?</i>

190
00:19:51.991 --> 00:19:53.503
We're here.

191
00:19:55.204 --> 00:19:57.351
There's a lot of guys with guns here.

192
00:19:57.375 --> 00:20:00.758
This goes bad. it's gonna go real bad

193
00:20:00.782 --> 00:20:02.629
<i>real fast.</i>

194
00:20:02.653 --> 00:20:04.321
Stand by.

195
00:20:04.588 --> 00:20:06.558
Something's happening here.

196
00:20:22.926 --> 00:20:24.396
What happened?

197
00:20:24.420 --> 00:20:26.944
<i>The security detail
of the Chinese delegation</i>

198
00:20:26.968 --> 00:20:30.117
<i>has asked all the other
delegates to ask their details</i>

199
00:20:30.141 --> 00:20:34.492
<i>to pretend that you don't exist
for the next 15 minutes.</i>

200
00:20:34.516 --> 00:20:38.099
<i>Pavlovich is in Cabana 14
with his detail.</i>

201
00:20:38.123 --> 00:20:39.436
<i>That's seven men.</i>

202
00:20:39.460 --> 00:20:40.972
<i>They're unaware of your arrival.</i>

203
00:20:40.996 --> 00:20:43.276
<i>Do it and get out.</i>

204
00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:45.671
Copy that. Stand by.

205
00:20:46.139 --> 00:20:47.718
What can I do?

206
00:20:47.742 --> 00:20:49.226
Nothing.

207
00:20:49.341 --> 00:20:50.637
I'll locate the target

208
00:20:50.661 --> 00:20:52.567
- and I'll give you the heads up.
- What can I do?

209
00:20:52.591 --> 00:20:53.730
Nothing.

210
00:20:57.161 --> 00:20:59.041
I'll keep one alive.

211
00:20:59.065 --> 00:21:02.347
I'll do what I can to get
Chase's location from him.

212
00:21:02.371 --> 00:21:04.853
but there isn't much time
to get him that antidote.

213
00:21:04.877 --> 00:21:06.534
Then hurry.

214
00:21:27.989 --> 00:21:29.766
<i>They're leaving me alone.</i>

215
00:21:30.194 --> 00:21:32.465
<i>For now. at least.</i>

216
00:21:34.510 --> 00:21:36.680
<i>I'm moving towards the cabana.</i>

217
00:22:27.609 --> 00:22:28.887
You there?

218
00:22:28.911 --> 00:22:31.234
- <i>Yeah.</i>
- I just saw two men.

219
00:22:31.258 --> 00:22:32.737
I think they're heading toward you.

220
00:22:32.761 --> 00:22:33.931
<i>Copy.</i>

221
00:23:22.585 --> 00:23:25.123
Who the fuck are you?

222
00:23:37.448 --> 00:23:40.053
Do you know who I am?

223
00:23:41.757 --> 00:23:44.094
You're the guy who killed the old man.

224
00:23:49.338 --> 00:23:51.777
And I'm the guy who got you.

225
00:24:08.744 --> 00:24:10.824
<i>I got one of 'em here.</i>

226
00:24:10.848 --> 00:24:13.497
<i>I'm gonna do the best I can
to get the location from him.</i>

227
00:24:13.521 --> 00:24:15.306
We don't need him.

228
00:24:16.159 --> 00:24:17.642
I found it.

229
00:24:30.760 --> 00:24:32.195
It's done.

230
00:24:32.597 --> 00:24:34.811
My colleagues will sort out the story.

231
00:24:34.835 --> 00:24:37.868
Oh. You're ahead of me.

232
00:24:38.509 --> 00:24:39.988
It died.

233
00:24:41.882 --> 00:24:43.719
Harold.

234
00:24:48.001 --> 00:24:49.838
I'm glad you came.

235
00:24:50.300 --> 00:24:52.203
It was good to see you again.

236
00:25:01.322 --> 00:25:03.000
You said it yourself.

237
00:25:03.024 --> 00:25:05.937
You would never have let me
anywhere near Angela.

238
00:25:15.048 --> 00:25:16.752
I'm sorry.

239
00:25:17.754 --> 00:25:19.858
Yeah. I'll bet.

240
00:25:58.336 --> 00:25:59.948
Oh. no.

241
00:25:59.972 --> 00:26:02.544
Ah. shit.

242
00:26:03.279 --> 00:26:06.819
Hey. Hey. Hey.

243
00:26:13.833 --> 00:26:15.146
Okay.

244
00:26:17.875 --> 00:26:19.220
I found him.

245
00:26:19.244 --> 00:26:20.790
- <i>Is he alive?</i>
- I don't know.

246
00:26:20.814 --> 00:26:22.894
<i>You know how to check his pulse?
Beside the windpipe.</i>

247
00:26:22.918 --> 00:26:24.521
Uh. hold on.

248
00:26:25.289 --> 00:26:27.693
I can't tell. M-Maybe?

249
00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:30.872
<i>- Did you give him the antidote?</i>
- No. On it.

250
00:26:32.704 --> 00:26:34.617
<i>- Give him all three doses.</i>
- Yeah.

251
00:26:34.641 --> 00:26:36.155
<i>And the yellow one.</i>

252
00:26:36.179 --> 00:26:38.716
Okay. Oh. fuck.

253
00:26:39.785 --> 00:26:41.855
Okay. here we go.

254
00:26:43.693 --> 00:26:46.632
Okay.

255
00:27:01.662 --> 00:27:03.241
<i>Did that do anything?</i>

256
00:27:03.265 --> 00:27:04.681
No.

257
00:27:05.370 --> 00:27:07.966
<i>You said you know CPR. Do it.</i>

258
00:27:07.990 --> 00:27:10.255
All right. here we go.
Here we go. I got this.

259
00:29:05.385 --> 00:29:07.095
You're awake.

260
00:29:08.114 --> 00:29:09.995
Hey.

261
00:29:10.019 --> 00:29:12.534
- Where is this?
- It's-it's a safe house.

262
00:29:12.558 --> 00:29:14.337
It belonged to Morgan.

263
00:29:14.361 --> 00:29:15.973
Nobody had used it for a long time.

264
00:29:15.997 --> 00:29:18.345
- Look. nobody knows we're here.
- How did you...

265
00:29:18.369 --> 00:29:20.716
I had a little help getting you here.

266
00:29:20.740 --> 00:29:23.388
- Harold?
- Uh. no. no.

267
00:29:23.412 --> 00:29:25.459
Um. Julian. Morgan's partner.

268
00:29:25.483 --> 00:29:27.657
But it's just been us for a while now.

269
00:29:28.121 --> 00:29:30.169
You've been in and out
the last few days.

270
00:29:30.193 --> 00:29:32.173
We've been sitting still too long.

271
00:29:32.197 --> 00:29:33.642
No. no. No. no. we're safe here.

272
00:29:33.666 --> 00:29:35.011
- We're safe here.
- No. after what we did.

273
00:29:35.035 --> 00:29:37.216
- people are gonna come for us.
- We're safe.

274
00:29:37.240 --> 00:29:38.852
We're safe.

275
00:29:38.876 --> 00:29:41.591
No one knows we're here.

276
00:29:41.615 --> 00:29:43.423
We got away.

277
00:29:46.191 --> 00:29:48.905
No one? No one knows?

278
00:29:48.929 --> 00:29:52.056
Well. Julian knows.
but Morgan trusted him.

279
00:29:52.638 --> 00:29:54.494
- Harold?
- No.

280
00:29:54.518 --> 00:29:57.055
No. we didn't feel like it was
safe enough to reach out to him.

281
00:29:57.079 --> 00:29:59.461
Maybe. maybe one day. Here. drink.

282
00:30:03.593 --> 00:30:06.030
There's one more. isn't there?

283
00:30:07.801 --> 00:30:09.616
Yeah. there's one more.

284
00:30:10.825 --> 00:30:12.453
He's my kid.

285
00:30:12.477 --> 00:30:14.624
And no one can trace him to me.

286
00:30:14.648 --> 00:30:15.926
Anyone who'd want to find us

287
00:30:15.950 --> 00:30:18.532
doesn't even know Zoe McDonald exists.

288
00:30:18.556 --> 00:30:20.101
I was careful.

289
00:30:20.125 --> 00:30:23.932
Before Julian left. I made sure
I knew how to make sure.

290
00:30:24.255 --> 00:30:27.216
- This place is an island.
- Oh. okay.

291
00:30:27.240 --> 00:30:29.052
- Thank you.
- Okay.

292
00:30:33.553 --> 00:30:34.998
We are safe.

293
00:30:35.022 --> 00:30:38.026
We can stay here as long
as we need. as long as we want.

294
00:30:42.236 --> 00:30:44.734
You want to stay here
with me for a while?

295
00:31:07.119 --> 00:31:09.200
<i>When I was a little girl.</i>

296
00:31:09.224 --> 00:31:11.636
<i>I was afraid of the dark</i>

297
00:31:13.054 --> 00:31:15.598
<i>and all the things I couldn't see.</i>

298
00:31:19.936 --> 00:31:24.119
<i>The hopeful things that were
promised on faith alone...</i>

299
00:31:27.260 --> 00:31:29.112
<i>...and stories.</i>

300
00:31:30.366 --> 00:31:32.870
<i>I never trusted them.</i>

301
00:31:34.634 --> 00:31:37.739
<i>I couldn't imagine
how anyone ever could.</i>

302
00:31:44.400 --> 00:31:47.071
<i>Because in that darkness ahead...</i>

303
00:31:48.067 --> 00:31:50.550
<i>...what else was lurking?</i>

304
00:31:54.241 --> 00:31:57.047
<i>I've always been certain
there was always something else</i>

305
00:31:57.072 --> 00:31:58.942
<i>out in the dark.</i>

306
00:32:01.895 --> 00:32:04.634
But this... this...

307
00:32:06.371 --> 00:32:08.234
...feels different.

308
00:32:10.570 --> 00:32:14.687
With your dad. I always felt
like I-I needed to...

309
00:32:14.907 --> 00:32:16.791
defend myself

310
00:32:17.285 --> 00:32:19.206
from-from whatever

311
00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:21.744
was going to reveal itself
out of the unknown.

312
00:32:21.768 --> 00:32:24.408
whatever might be hiding
around every corner.

313
00:32:25.243 --> 00:32:29.049
<i>And you don't feel that now?</i>

314
00:32:30.486 --> 00:32:32.050
No.

315
00:32:32.724 --> 00:32:35.796
No. I don't.

316
00:32:37.500 --> 00:32:39.337
<i>You sound happy. Mom.</i>

317
00:32:40.840 --> 00:32:42.877
<i>You deserve that.</i>

318
00:32:44.348 --> 00:32:46.952
<i>Maybe I'll get to meet him sometime.</i>

319
00:33:06.108 --> 00:33:08.645
<i>Have you seen my glasses?</i>

320
00:33:09.414 --> 00:33:11.494
- What?
- My glasses.

321
00:33:11.518 --> 00:33:13.365
Feel like I just had 'em.

322
00:33:13.389 --> 00:33:14.633
I keep losing things.

323
00:33:14.657 --> 00:33:17.039
It's like
there are goblins in this house.

324
00:33:17.063 --> 00:33:19.834
Unlikely. Hey.

325
00:33:24.243 --> 00:33:26.347
That's it.

326
00:33:26.828 --> 00:33:28.806
You're losing your edge.

327
00:33:29.688 --> 00:33:31.224
Don't joke.

328
00:33:35.166 --> 00:33:37.837
<i>Is something concerning you?</i>

329
00:33:39.174 --> 00:33:41.011
No.

330
00:33:41.980 --> 00:33:44.655
I think that might be the problem.

331
00:33:46.188 --> 00:33:49.761
There's so many things
to be concerned about.

332
00:33:52.066 --> 00:33:56.784
<i>We left the world full
of questions without answers.</i>

333
00:33:56.808 --> 00:34:00.258
There's been nothing in the news
about the cartel

334
00:34:00.282 --> 00:34:03.331
because. wh-what. it-it fell apart?

335
00:34:03.355 --> 00:34:06.037
Because we were misled
about how close it was?

336
00:34:06.061 --> 00:34:09.388
Because we're still the only
people who know about it?

337
00:34:09.901 --> 00:34:13.384
Did the spook that you met
at the British police station.

338
00:34:13.408 --> 00:34:16.181
did he tell any of his friends?

339
00:34:17.630 --> 00:34:21.108
Could anything stop them
from finding us if he did?

340
00:34:24.263 --> 00:34:27.880
<i>There's a German word that escapes me</i>

341
00:34:27.904 --> 00:34:31.554
<i>for an idea that pretends
not to be seen</i>

342
00:34:31.578 --> 00:34:33.691
<i>because once it's acknowledged.</i>

343
00:34:33.715 --> 00:34:36.821
<i>nobody can pretend it isn't true.</i>

344
00:34:42.400 --> 00:34:44.804
Wish I could remember.

345
00:34:46.742 --> 00:34:48.855
<i>If these are things
to be concerned about.</i>

346
00:34:48.879 --> 00:34:50.888
<i>why do you think
you've been ignoring them?</i>

347
00:35:00.971 --> 00:35:04.945
Because I don't want this to change.

348
00:35:09.619 --> 00:35:11.993
I don't want this to end.

349
00:37:24.524 --> 00:37:25.735
Hey. Jan. order up.

350
00:37:25.759 --> 00:37:27.296
Thanks.

351
00:37:45.968 --> 00:37:47.879
Doing okay. Joe?

352
00:38:16.001 --> 00:38:17.669
This is Zoe.

353
00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:21.403
Zoe. this is my daughter Emily.

354
00:38:21.730 --> 00:38:24.302
It's so nice to finally meet you.

355
00:38:24.651 --> 00:38:26.421
Nice to meet you. too.

356
00:38:27.951 --> 00:38:30.064
Wasn't easy finding you.

357
00:38:30.088 --> 00:38:32.102
I'm so sorry. we thought...

358
00:38:32.126 --> 00:38:35.275
It's okay. it's okay.

359
00:38:35.299 --> 00:38:37.406
I'm just really glad you're here.

360
00:38:38.097 --> 00:38:40.201
I'm really glad that you're okay.

361
00:38:41.711 --> 00:38:43.448
Are you okay?

362
00:38:47.389 --> 00:38:49.026
I'm here.

363
00:38:49.761 --> 00:38:51.407
I'm in one piece.

364
00:38:52.800 --> 00:38:54.313
I'll tell you all about it. okay?

365
00:38:54.337 --> 00:38:55.906
I really will.

366
00:38:57.109 --> 00:38:59.046
I want you to know.

367
00:39:00.783 --> 00:39:02.520
But not now.

368
00:39:03.455 --> 00:39:06.519
Now time is short. and I need your help.

369
00:39:17.516 --> 00:39:20.407
You two have been
pretty isolated here. so...

370
00:39:21.075 --> 00:39:23.594
you don't know about what
happened to Harold. do you?

371
00:39:23.744 --> 00:39:25.120
What happened?

372
00:39:25.732 --> 00:39:27.289
He's gone.

373
00:39:28.172 --> 00:39:29.316
Gone?

374
00:39:29.340 --> 00:39:32.656
He went to see his ex-wife.
to get her help.

375
00:39:32.680 --> 00:39:34.922
to save you and I both.

376
00:39:35.419 --> 00:39:37.332
She has him somewhere.

377
00:39:37.356 --> 00:39:39.169
And she's trying to use him to bargain

378
00:39:39.193 --> 00:39:41.574
for control of the Meshbahar deposit.

379
00:39:41.598 --> 00:39:43.681
Bargain with who?

380
00:39:44.640 --> 00:39:46.216
I thought it was taken from Pavlovich

381
00:39:46.240 --> 00:39:49.123
by some. you know. yahoos in the valley.

382
00:39:50.466 --> 00:39:52.319
In a manner of speaking.

383
00:39:53.702 --> 00:39:56.193
Who controls the deposit now?

384
00:39:57.797 --> 00:39:59.200
Me.

385
00:40:00.406 --> 00:40:02.449
And what remains of the family.

386
00:40:02.473 --> 00:40:04.662
I have been asked to speak for them.

387
00:40:04.686 --> 00:40:07.121
I have been asked to help
decide what to do.

388
00:40:08.118 --> 00:40:11.800
Marion is using Harold to fuck with me.

389
00:40:11.824 --> 00:40:13.138
And I don't want to be fucked with.

390
00:40:13.162 --> 00:40:15.296
Not now and not about this.

391
00:40:15.699 --> 00:40:18.037
So I'm going to get him back.

392
00:40:18.549 --> 00:40:20.843
And I need you in order to do it.

393
00:40:21.377 --> 00:40:23.157
Yeah. Yes.

394
00:40:23.181 --> 00:40:25.829
- You're gonna get me what I need.
- Yes.

395
00:40:25.853 --> 00:40:27.099
No matter what I ask.

396
00:40:27.123 --> 00:40:29.310
Mm-hmm. yes. of course.

397
00:40:30.875 --> 00:40:33.080
I need access to Lou Barlow.

398
00:40:36.108 --> 00:40:39.123
I need you to help me
get inside Marion's armor.

399
00:40:39.147 --> 00:40:42.196
Lou Barlow had
the connections to do that.

400
00:40:42.220 --> 00:40:44.283
It's the only way to do it.

401
00:40:45.367 --> 00:40:48.007
Harold's life is hanging in the balance.

402
00:40:48.031 --> 00:40:51.003
I know that you may not want
to open that door again.

403
00:40:51.557 --> 00:40:53.626
but I need you to.

404
00:40:54.668 --> 00:40:56.190
Who is Lou Barlow?

405
00:40:56.214 --> 00:40:59.186
Dad. please.

406
00:40:59.921 --> 00:41:01.467
Will you help me?

407
00:41:01.491 --> 00:41:02.669
Well.

408
00:41:02.693 --> 00:41:05.098
of course I'm gonna help you.

409
00:41:08.491 --> 00:41:11.129
There are better ways to do this.

410
00:41:14.229 --> 00:41:16.530
I can show you. Em. I promise.

411
00:41:16.554 --> 00:41:18.691
Who is Lou Barlow?

412
00:41:26.333 --> 00:41:27.952
I was.

413
00:41:30.911 --> 00:41:32.706
And what did you do?

414
00:41:34.657 --> 00:41:36.939
You-you told me
about what you used to do.

415
00:41:36.963 --> 00:41:38.741
You told me about the ugliest violence.

416
00:41:38.765 --> 00:41:40.478
- What else could this be?
- Yeah...

417
00:41:40.502 --> 00:41:43.884
No. I told you
some of the things I used to do.

418
00:41:46.300 --> 00:41:47.735
Some things...

419
00:41:49.866 --> 00:41:53.811
There are things that are
uglier than violence.

420
00:41:56.334 --> 00:41:59.216
Em. we're gonna get him back.

421
00:41:59.240 --> 00:42:01.887
I will stop at nothing to do it.

422
00:42:01.911 --> 00:42:03.504
I will find a way.

423
00:42:03.529 --> 00:42:06.736
I've already found a way. Dad.

424
00:42:07.991 --> 00:42:09.620
There are better ways to get to Marion.

425
00:42:09.644 --> 00:42:11.240
- This is the way to do it.
- Emily...

426
00:42:11.264 --> 00:42:12.643
This is the best way to do it.

427
00:42:12.667 --> 00:42:15.681
I've known Marion
since before you were born.

428
00:42:15.705 --> 00:42:17.619
You're gonna have to trust me...

429
00:42:17.643 --> 00:42:19.837
This is the way that I want to do it.

430
00:42:24.190 --> 00:42:28.631
Harold Harper sacrificed himself
for you and for me.

431
00:42:29.867 --> 00:42:32.049
All I'm asking of you is to do

432
00:42:32.073 --> 00:42:34.935
what you taught me to do.

433
00:42:35.646 --> 00:42:37.125
To do what we owe him.

434
00:42:37.149 --> 00:42:38.895
To save his life.

435
00:42:38.919 --> 00:42:41.401
And you want to debate about
whether or not it might be

436
00:42:41.425 --> 00:42:43.904
- too unpleasant to try?
- No. no. we're not debating.

437
00:42:43.928 --> 00:42:45.612
No. we aren't.

438
00:42:56.221 --> 00:42:58.725
The only thing I can't figure out.

439
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:01.740
Are you saying no

440
00:43:01.764 --> 00:43:04.703
because you don't want to do
what it would take

441
00:43:04.943 --> 00:43:07.217
or because you don't want her
to see you do it?

442
00:43:18.432 --> 00:43:20.947
- Hmm.
- Who is that?

443
00:43:20.971 --> 00:43:22.505
They're here to get us. Zoe.

444
00:43:22.775 --> 00:43:24.586
and take us to a plane
that I have waiting.

445
00:43:24.610 --> 00:43:26.723
Get us?

446
00:43:26.747 --> 00:43:29.253
Who is that. Emily?

447
00:43:32.117 --> 00:43:37.069
I'm in control
of an irreplaceable thing.

448
00:43:38.605 --> 00:43:41.787
There isn't a government
on Earth that doesn't need it.

449
00:43:41.811 --> 00:43:45.839
that isn't terrified
of their enemies getting it.

450
00:43:46.320 --> 00:43:51.007
So. when I ask
for a little help from the FBI

451
00:43:51.031 --> 00:43:53.388
tapping Zoe's son's phone...

452
00:43:54.482 --> 00:43:56.520
...or finding you here...

453
00:43:57.696 --> 00:44:00.668
...or transporting you
out of the country...

454
00:44:01.417 --> 00:44:04.690
Parwana Hamzad gets whatever she wants.

455
00:44:08.231 --> 00:44:09.780
Yeah.

456
00:44:10.789 --> 00:44:12.324
She does.

